org.sbml.displaysbml
Class SBML2LaTeX

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.displaysbml.StringOperations
      org.sbml.displaysbml.LaTeX
          org.sbml.displaysbml.SBML2LaTeX
All Implemented Interfaces:
DisplaySBML, libsbmlConstants
public class SBML2LaTeX
extends LaTeX
implements libsbmlConstants, DisplaySBML

This class displays the whole information content of an SBML model in a LaTeX file which can then be further processed, i.e., to a PDF file.

Since:
2.0
Version:
1.0
Author:
Andreas Dräger, Dieudonne Motsou Wouamba

This variable is needed to decide whether a method should write a document head and tail for the LaTeX output.

printNameIfAvailable

private boolean printNameIfAvailable
If true species (reactants, modifiers and products) in reaction equations will be displayed with their name if they have one. By default the ids of the species are used in these equations.

landscape

private boolean landscape
If true this will produce LaTeX files for for entirely landscape documents

typewriter

private boolean typewriter
If true ids are set in typewriter font (default).

showPredefinedUnitDeclarations

private boolean showPredefinedUnitDeclarations
If true predefined SBML units will be made explicitly if not overridden in the model.

titlepage

private boolean titlepage
If true a title page will be created by LaTeX for the resulting document. Otherwise there will only be a title on top of the first page.

checkConsistency

private boolean checkConsistency
If true a section of all errors found in the SBML file are printed at the end of the document

includeMIRIAM

private boolean includeMIRIAM
If true MIRIAM annotations are included into the model report. This process takes a bit time due to the necessary connection to EBI's web-service.

arrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable

private boolean arrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable
This switch allows to change the way how the reactants, modifiers and products are presented in each reaction. If true a table is created containing the identifiers of each reactant, modifier and product together with the respective name. If false (default), a subsection for each one of the three groups of participants is created giving all details of each participant.

Constructor Detail

SBML2LaTeX

public SBML2LaTeX()
Constructs a new instance of LaTeX export. For each document to be translated a new instance has to be created. Here default values are used (A4 paper, 11pt, portrait, fancy headings, no titlepage).

SBML2LaTeX

public SBML2LaTeX(boolean landscape,
                  boolean typeWriter,
                  short fontSize,
                  String paperSize,
                  boolean addPredefinedUnits,
                  boolean titlepage,
                  boolean printNameIfAvailable)
Constructs a new instance of LaTeX export. For each document to be translated a new instance has to be created. This constructor allows you to set many properties of the resulting LaTeX file.

Parameters:
landscape - If true the whole document will be set to landscape format, otherwise portrait.
typeWriter - If true ids are set in typewriter font (default). Otherwise the regular font is used.
fontSize - The size of the font to be used here. The default is 11. Allowed values are 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 14, 16 and 17.
paperSize - Allowed are
  • letter
  • legal
  • executive
  • a* where * stands for values from 0 thru 9
  • b*
  • c*
  • d*
addPredefinedUnits - If true predefined SBML units will be made explicitly if not overridden in the model.
titlepage - if true a title page will be created for the model report. Default is false (just a caption).

getNameOrID

private StringBuffer getNameOrID(SBase sbase,
                                 boolean mathMode)
If the field printNameIfAvailable is false this method returns a the id of the given SBase. If printNameIfAvailable is true this method looks for the name of the given SBase and will return it.

Parameters:
sbase - the SBase, whose name or id is to be returned.
mathMode - if true this method returns the name typesetted in mathmode, i.e., mathrm for names and mathtt for ids, otherwise texttt will be used for ids and normalfont (nothing) will be used for names.
Returns:
The name or the ID of the SBase (according to the field printNameIfAvailable), whose LaTeX special symbols are masked and which is type set in typewriter font if it is an id. The mathmode argument decides if mathtt or mathrm has to be used.
